body_html:
That's interesting. It still says that, even though -O2 is being passed.

CentOS7 is definitely in our support matrix. However this is a problem Bazel might need to solve. There seems to be a bug tracking this. bazelbuild/bazel#1762 It might help if you tell them your OS and GCC version combos.

Since this is only a warning, no workaround should be necessary.

cc: @wichtounet @vladfi1
See also: tensorflow/serving#137

body:
That's interesting. It still says that, even though `-O2` is being passed.

CentOS7 is definitely in our support matrix. However this is a problem Bazel might need to solve. There seems to be a bug tracking this. https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/1762 It might help if you tell them your OS and GCC version combos.

Since this is only a warning, no workaround should be necessary.

cc: @wichtounet @vladfi1
See also: https://github.com/tensorflow/serving/issues/137
